#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Aniccavagga"
msgstr "1. Impermanence"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 4. Bāhirāniccasutta → aniccaṃ 2; bāhiraṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Bāhirāniccasutta"
msgstr "4. The Exterior as Impermanent"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli4.3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.4:1.1"
msgid "“Rūpā, bhikkhave, aniccā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, sights are impermanent."

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.2"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ;"
msgstr "What’s impermanent is suffering."

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.3"
msgid "yaṃ dukkhaṃ tadanattā."
msgstr "What’s suffering is not-self."

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.4"
msgid ""
"Yadanattā taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And what’s not-self should be truly seen with proper understanding like this:"
" ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.5"
msgid "Saddā …"
msgstr "Sounds,"

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.6"
msgid "gandhā …"
msgstr "smells,"

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.7"
msgid "rasā …"
msgstr "tastes,"

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.8"
msgid "phoṭṭhabbā …"
msgstr "touches,"

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.9"
msgid "dhammā aniccā."
msgstr "and thoughts are impermanent."

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.10"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ;"
msgstr "What’s impermanent is suffering."

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.11"
msgid "yaṃ dukkhaṃ tadanattā."
msgstr "What’s suffering is not-self."

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.12"
msgid ""
"Yadanattā taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And what’s not-self should be truly seen with proper understanding like this:"
" ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.13"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpesupi nibbindati, saddesupi "
"nibbindati, gandhesupi nibbindati, rasesupi nibbindati, phoṭṭhabbesupi "
"nibbindati, dhammesupi nibbindati."
msgstr ""
"Seeing this, a learned noble disciple becomes disillusioned with sights, "
"sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts."

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.14"
msgid ""
"Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned they become dispassionate. Being dispassionate they’re "
"freed. When freed, they know ‘it is freed’."

msgctxt "sn35.4:1.15"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.4:1.16"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
